        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 5:01PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Davis, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Davis, Camp Mitre Peak, Davis Mountains State Park, Indian
Lodge, and Fort Davis National Historical Site.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
